chide
	v. scold or rebuke
parsimonious
	adj. excessively sparing or frugal
languid
	adj. (of a person, manner, or gesture) displaying or having a disinclination for physical exertion or effort; slow and relaxed
perspicacious
	adj. having a ready insight into and understanding of things
sagacious
	adj.having or showing keen mental discernment and good judgement
mellifluous
	adj. (of a voice or words) sweet or musical; pleasant to hear
dramaturgy
	n. the theory and practice of dramatic composition
contrivance
	n. the use of skill to bring something about or create something
dilettantes
	n. a person who cultivates an area of interest, such as the arts, without real commitment or knowledge